Package: boundarylogic
Type: Package
Title: Biplot-Based Decision Boundary Interpretability for Classification Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Adriaan", "Rowan", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "adriaan@example.com")
Description: Provides a biplot-based post hoc explanation framework for binary
    classification models. Projects high-dimensional data into a two-dimensional
    PCA or CVA biplot space, approximates model decision boundaries in that
    reduced space, identifies counterfactual observations, and supports both
    local and global model interpretability analyses including Shapley value
    attribution and variable-importance-by-distance summaries.
